This paper deals with character-based neural machine translation models, which are primarily used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper explores the use of convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in computer vision, falling under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the issue of model robustness, which is a common concern in neural networks, falling under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
